# External Storage

The following external folders are available in your workspace:

{% if external_mounts.ro %}
## Read-Only Mounts (`./external/ro/`)

These folders are mounted read-only. You can read files but **cannot create, modify, or delete** them.

{% for mount in external_mounts.ro %}
- `./external/ro/{{ mount.name }}/` {% if mount.description %}- {{ mount.description }}{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if external_mounts.rw %}
## Read-Write Mounts (`./external/rw/`)

These folders allow both reading and writing. Files you create or modify here will be visible to the host system.

{% for mount in external_mounts.rw %}
- `./external/rw/{{ mount.name }}/` {% if mount.description %}- {{ mount.description }}{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if external_mounts.persistent %}
## Persistent Storage (`./external/persistent/`)

This folder persists across sessions. Files you save here will be available in future sessions.

**IMPORTANT:** When the user asks to save something "permanently", "persistently", "across sessions", or "for later use", **always save to `./external/persistent/`**.

**Use for:**
- Files the user explicitly wants to keep permanently
- Cached data you want to reuse between sessions
- Output files to share across multiple sessions
- Configuration or state that should survive session cleanup

{% endif %}

{% if external_mounts.user_ro %}
## User-Specific Read-Only Mounts (`./external/user-ro/`)

These folders are mounted specifically for your user account, read-only:

{% for mount in external_mounts.user_ro %}
- `./external/user-ro/{{ mount.name }}/` {% if mount.description %}- {{ mount.description }}{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if external_mounts.user_rw %}
## User-Specific Read-Write Mounts (`./external/user-rw/`)

These folders are mounted specifically for your user account, read-write:

{% for mount in external_mounts.user_rw %}
- `./external/user-rw/{{ mount.name }}/` {% if mount.description %}- {{ mount.description }}{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

## Important Notes

1. **Read-only access**: You cannot write to `./external/ro/` or `./external/user-ro/` paths. Attempts will fail with "read-only external mount" error.
2. **Relative paths**: Access mounts using relative paths like `./external/ro/downloads/file.txt`.
3. **File changes**: Changes to writable mounts and `./external/persistent/` are immediately visible to the host system.

